Table I shows the performance comparisons on MNIST, FashionMNIST, GTSRB and CIFAR-101010 datasets with the obtained global model after K=400ğ¾400K=400 VEFL rounds when umax=20.12superscriptumax20.12\mathrm{u}^{\mathrm{max}}=20.12 m/s, tth=5superscripttth5\mathrm{t}^{\mathrm{th}}=5 s and Îâ€‹(k)=1000Îğ‘˜1000\Xi(k)=1000 units.
Under the resource-constrained scenario, it can be observed that both FDPC and PDPC perform similarly while the baselines lag significantly.
Furthermore, even without constraints, AFA-CD fails to perform reasonably in GTSRB and CIFAR-101010 datasets.
Moreover, the proposed schemes achieve performance comparable to FedProx W/O constraints, which validates the effectiveness of our proposed solutions under extreme resource constraints.
